git-ftp - (Linux/Debian)

# apt install git-ftp

1) Set up a user by typing:
git config git-ftp.user 'FTPUserName'

2) Configure your server's FTP path:
git config git-ftp.url ftp.example.net/public_html/optional1
/optional2

NOTE: It is interesting to inform the root folder of your server, ex: public_html.
You can enter as many subdirectories as you want:
/optional1
/optional2

3) Set up a password:
git config git-ftp.password 'yourFTPPassword'

4) When submitting the project for the first time to your server you should run:
git ftp init
